President Muhammadu Buhari has reacted to the death of Isa Pantami’s daughter, Aisha.  Reacting on Tuesday, Buhari commiserated with the Minister of Communication and Digital Economy, Dr Isa Pantami. A statement signed by his spokesman, Garba Shehu said that the president had earlier placed a call to the minister on Monday evening. It said that Buhari condoled with all members of the family on the sad event, urging comfort in the teachings of the Holy Prophet on the transient nature of life. President Buhari prayed that Allah will accept the soul of the departed, and grant her Jannah tul Firdaus, according to the brief statement. By Jessica Dogo Abuja - The Minister of Communications and Digital Economy, Dr Isa Pantami, has ordered the Nigerian Communications Commission (NCC) to immediately ensure that issues regarding automatic voicemails are addressed on all existing phone lines in the country. In a statement signed by Mrs Uwa Suleiman, Spokesperson to… November 15, 2019 In "News" ABUJA - Amid growing concern that Fifth Generation Mobile Networks, popularly called 5G has very negative health implications, the Nigerian government has denied issuing any 5G licence.The Minister of Communication and Digital Economy, Dr. Isa Pantami, in a statement issued on Saturday and sent to Sundiata Post, clarified on what… April 4, 2020 In "News" The Late Isa Funtua who died at 87 years old, was an associate of President Muhammadu Buhari, had in one of his last interviews said he is not a member of any cabal but a “cabal myself.” The Late Funtua, is among those whom critics of the Buhari administration refer… July 21, 2020 In "Interview"